id: pm-8mxg
title: "pm package init --declarative: scaffold a composeExtension blueprint starter + author-time preflight test"
description: "Add a `--declarative` flag to `pm package init` that scaffolds the SDK's flagship declarative authoring loop. Today every scaffolded starter (all 9 --capability variants) authors via imperative `defineExtension({ activate })` and tests via the runtime helpers (activateExtensionForTest/assertRegistered*/runRegistered*/deactivateExtensionForTest). NONE demonstrates `composeExtension`/`defineExtensionBlueprint` (the declarative loop SDK.md calls 'the capstone of the author -> register -> test loop') or the author-time preflight capstone (`assertExtensionPreflight`/`preflightExtension`) or the ergonomic runtime capstone (`createExtensionTestHarness`). A new author who runs `pm package init` never discovers the easiest, best-practice authoring path. The `--declarative` starter generates index.ts as `defineExtensionBlueprint` + `composeExtension(blueprint)` and index.test.ts as `assertExtensionPreflight(blueprint, { identity, target })` (author-time) + `createExtensionTestHarness(module)` (runtime) + teardown. Scoped to package-mode (composeExtension is a runtime SDK value import; bundled extension-only installs stay import-free per SDK.md) and the commands capability (the canonical composeExtension example); other capabilities and extension-mode error clearly. Discovered by dogfooding the full scaffold matrix in a temp workspace (all 9 imperative starters typecheck + pass their generated tests). Goal: project management = context management — make creating new packages as easy and customizable as possible."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[5]: "area:extensions","area:packages","area:sdk",dx,pm-cli
created_at: "2026-06-24T18:26:57.582Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-24T18:46:03.585Z"
author: claude-code-agent
goal: project management = context management
value: "Surfaces the declarative composeExtension authoring loop + author-time preflight capstone in the scaffold so package authors discover and adopt the easiest, best-practice path on first `pm package init`."
parent: pm-ugqx
resolution: "Added `pm package init --declarative` — a package-mode, commands-capability blueprint starter that scaffolds `defineExtensionBlueprint` → `composeExtension(blueprint)` (index.ts) plus an index.test.ts exercising the author-time `assertExtensionPreflight` capstone and the runtime `createExtensionTestHarness`. Wired the flag through register-setup/extension/completion/cli-contracts; documented in SDK.md."
expected_result: "`pm package init <path> --declarative` generates a typecheck-clean, test-passing composeExtension starter; extension-mode, non-commands `--capability`, and non-init use each return a clear USAGE error; 100% coverage and all quality gates stay green."
actual_result: "Delivered as specified: scaffold generates the declarative starter (style=declarative), all three error paths return exit 2, 5049 tests pass at 100/100/100/100 coverage, typecheck/static-quality/docs-skills/contracts gates green, and the composed module installs + dispatches end-to-end in a dogfooded temp workspace."
