learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-24T18:45:22.620Z",claude-code-agent,"A declarative scaffolded package's index.ts has a runtime VALUE import of composeExtension from @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk (unlike the imperative starter, whose only SDK import is the erased `ExtensionApi` type). So an end-to-end spawnSync dispatch test must link the host SDK into the temp workspace (node_modules/@unbrained/pm-cli -> repo root) or the composed module fails to load — this is exactly why --declarative is package-mode-only (the SDK is a linked dependency) and why the import-free extension-only starters must NOT use composeExtension. The imperative spawn test needs no such link because its type-only import is stripped on load."
